s feature the way you want to.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Here&#8217;s a quick tutorial on how to add a CTA to your slidedecks:</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>STEP ONE : </strong>Select &#8216;<strong>Content</strong>&#8216; from the &#8216;<strong>Options</strong>&#8216; dropdown menu</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CTAOptions.png\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-17090 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CTAOptions-580x461.png\" alt=\"CTA Options\" width=\"580\" height=\"461\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>STEP TWO : </strong>Select &#8216;<strong>ON</strong>&#8216; button in the &#8216;<strong>Enable CTA&#8217;</strong> option and customize your CTA button</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CTAEnable.png\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-17091 aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/CTAEnable-580x463.png\" alt=\"Enable CTA\" width=\"580\" height=\"463\" /></a></p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s how the CTA looks like on your sliders:</p>\n<div class=\"slidedeck-link\"><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/how-to-add-call-to-action-buttons-on-your-wordpress-image-slider/#SlideDeck-17094\">My SlideDeck <small>[see the SlideDeck]</small></a></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can also add an<strong> image as a CTA</strong>, as explained <a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/blog/slidedeck-version-3-3-4-released/\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>That is all you need to do to make your visitors click on your sliders !</p>\n<p>Need any help? Just a drop a note at <a href=\"support@slidedeck.com\" target=\"_blank\">support@slidedeck.com</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<br/><br/><a href=\"http://www.slidedeck.com/pricing/?utm_source=feed_ad&utm_medium=banner&utm_campaign=sd_blog\"><img src=\"//s3.amazonaws.com/assets-slidedeck2/wp-content/themes/slidedeck2/images/sd-rss.jpg\" alt=\"Easily create AWESOM